01/03/2011
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia -- Interior ministers of nine Southeast European countries signed a memorandum Monday (February 28th) on co-operation in the fight against human trafficking.
The agreement envisions the establishment of joint investigative teams to deal with the phenomenon.
The interior ministers of Slovenia, Bulgaria, Serbia, Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Macedonia, Moldova, Montenegro and Romania participated in the meeting in Ljubljana dedicated to regional police co-operation.
(STA, Tanjug, Makfax - 28/02/11)
